The paper deals with detecting dominant clusters in large data sets, which is a problem in data science and machine learning. The use of Evolutionary Game Theory and the development of a scalable algorithm suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of localized infection immunization dynamics and candidate infective vertex search methods suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The focus on efficiency and detection quality suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of Apache Spark for parallelization suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of affinity graphs suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category.
